[Category:1995 in Lithuanian football]]\n[[Category:1996 in Lithuanian football]]\n[[Category:1995\u201396 in European association football leagues|Lith]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football league season\n|season           = 1995\u201396\n|dates            = \n|competition      = [[A Lyga]]\n|winners          = <!-- (th title) -->\n|relegated        = \n|continentalcup1  = \n|continentalcup1 qualifiers = \n|continentalcup2  = \n|continentalcup2 qualifiers = \n|continentalcup3  = \n|continentalcup3 qualifiers = \n|league topscorer = \n|biggest home win = \n|biggest away win = \n|highest scoring  = \n|matches          = \n|total goals      = \n|prevseason = [[1994\u201395 A Lyga|1994\u201395]]\n|nextseason = [[1996\u201397 A Lyga|1996\u201397]]\n|updated    = \n}}\nStatistics of [[A Lyga]] for the 1995\u201396 season. It was contested by 15 teams, and [[Inkaras-Grifas Kaunas]] won the championship.\n\n==First round==\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n\n|team1=\u017dAL|name_\u017dAL=[[FK \u017dalgiris|\u017dalgiris]]\n|team2=INK|name_INK=[[FK Inkaras Kaunas|Inkaras-Grifas]]\n|team3=KAR|name_KAR=[[FK Kareda Kaunas|Kareda-Sakalas]]\n|team4=PSK|name_PSK=[[FK Atlantas|Aras]]\n|team5=FBK|name_FBK=[[FBK Kaunas]]\n|team6=PAN|name_PAN=[[FK Panerys Vilnius|Panerys]]\n|team7=EKR|name_EKR=[[FK Ekranas|Ekranas]]\n|team8=\u017dAL2|name_\u017dAL2=[[\u017dalgiris-2 Vilnius|\u017dalgiris-2]]\n|team9=KLA|name_KLA=[[FK Sirijus Klaip\u0117da|JR Klaip\u0117da]]\n|team10=BAN|name_BAN=[[FK Banga Garg\u017edai|Banga]]\n|team11=LOK|name_LOK=[[Lokomotyvas Vilnius|Lokomotyvas]]\n|team12=TAU|name_TAU=[[FK Tauras Taurag\u0117|Tauras]]\n|team13=MAS|name_MAS=[[FK Mastis Tel\u0161iai|Mastis]]\n|team14=UKM|name_UKM=[[FK Ukmerg\u0117|Ukmerg\u0117]]\n|team15=ALS|name_ALS=[[JR Alsa Vilnius|Alsa-Panerys]]\n|win_\u017dAL=13|draw_\u017dAL=1|loss_\u017dAL=0|gf_\u017dAL=63|ga_\u017dAL=7\n|win_INK=12|draw_INK=2|loss_INK=0|gf_INK=37|ga_INK=7\n|win_KAR=11|draw_KAR=0|loss_KAR=3|gf_KAR=3